TY  - JOUR
T1  - Effects of International Diversity and Product Diversity on the Performance of Multinational Firms
AU  - Tallman, Stephen
AU  - Li, Jiatao
Y1  - 1996/02/01
PY  - 1996
DA  - 1996/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256635
DO  - 10.5465/256635
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 179
EP  - 196
VL  - 39
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examined the relationships among international diversity, product diversity, and firm performance. For a sample of large American industrial multinational enterprises (MNEs), it showed a consistent quadratic relationship between product diversification and MNE performance but minimal performance differences across different measures of international diversity. Analysis of the interactions of international diversity and product diversity indicates a weak effect from increasing internationalization on the performance effect of product diversity.
AB  - This study examined the relationships among international diversity, product diversity, and firm performance. For a sample of large American industrial multinational enterprises (MNEs), it showed a consistent quadratic relationship between product diversification and MNE performance but minimal performance differences across different measures of international diversity. Analysis of the interactions of international diversity and product diversity indicates a weak effect from increasing internationalization on the performance effect of product diversity.
